-- Italy May Name Paolo Romani as Industry Minister Today, Messaggero Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-04T06:06:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/italy-may-name-paolo-romani-as-industry-minister-today-messaggero-says.html
Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  may name Paolo Romani Industry Minister as soon as
this afternoon, daily Il Messaggero reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Claudio Scajola  resigned as industry minister in May as a
court probed possible improprieties in his purchase of an
apartment in Rome.  Romani is currently deputy minister of communications.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  